      "span_text": "Haemorrhage is still a major cause of trauma mortality and accounts for 31% of deaths in the first hour after injury.  The American College of Surgeons' Advanced Trauma Life Support (ATLS) course mandates the insertion of two large-bore intravenous (IV) lines or the equivalent for patients with trauma.",
